The phyglos Catalog
===================

The phyglos Catalog is a BANDIT catalog used to raise the phy GNU/linux operating
system. The catalog contains the bundles of funcionality capable of raising a new
phy system from a supported Linux distribution.


How to use
==========

This catalog is used by the BANDIT toolkit to raise a new phy system. See the
BANDIT documentation (https://docs.phyglos.org/bandit) to learn how to use the
toolkit to install and remove bundles and packages.

Status
======

The phyglos catalog is in STABLE status. With this catalog the BANDIT can create
a new TARGET system and install phyglos in a free disk partition of the HOST system.

More information
================

The COPYING file contains the GNU License for this software.
The RELEASE file describes the main changes in this release.

See https://docs.phyglos.org/phyglos for more information.


